text:
ACC Power Poll: Clemson prepares for Notre Dame 
By Garry Smits Wed, Sep 30, 2015 @ 8:13 pm | updated Wed, Sep 30, 2015 @ 8:28 pm 
ACC POWER POLL 
1. CLEMSON (3-0) 
Playing Notre Dame might be most meaningful non-conference game since some of the classics against Georgia. 
2. FLORIDA STATE (3-0) 
Wake Forest may bear the brunt of ’Noles’ frustration after the offense’s horrid night at BC. 
3. N.C. STATE (4-0) 
OK, play time’s over. Finally getting to league games after a soft early schedule. 
4. DUKE (3-1) 
Huge victory over Georgia Tech gives Blue Devils thoughts of Charlotte in December. 
5. PITTSBURGH (2-1) 
Panthers probably needed the off-week to put the brutal loss to Iowa behind them. 
6. MIAMI (3-0) 
Hurricanes have insane 18-3 record on Thursday nights. 
7. NORTH CAROLINA (3-1) 
Offense has gotten back on the rails after loss to South Carolina but against who? 
8. GEORGIA TECH (2-2) 
Rushing yardage has declined each week since gaining 476 yards in opener against Alcorn. 
9. BOSTON COLLEGE (3-1) 
Hitting the road for three of the next four games. 
10. VIRGINIA TECH (2-2) 
Bud Foster’s defense let East Carolina’s James Summers, a JUCO WR who was converted to QB, light his team up for 279 total yards in three quarters. 
11. SYRACUSE (3-1) 
Give the Orange credit for never letting LSU take total control of the game. 
12. LOUISVILLE (1-3) 
Cardinals thank their lucky stars for the FCS. 
13. VIRGINIA (1-3) 
Cavaliers mailed it in against Boise with five turnovers, only 273 total yards. 
14. WAKE FOREST (2-2) 
Tough to go against FSU with one of nation’s worst running games and turnover margins. 
Garry Smits The Times-Union
